==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overbalance
<hw>O`ver*bal"ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To exceed equality with; to outweigh.</def>
<rj><au>Locke.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To cause to lose balance or equilibrium.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overbalance</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overbalance
<hw>O"ver*bal`ance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Excess of
weight or value; something more than an equivalent; <as>as, an
<ex>overbalance</ex> of exports</as>.</def> <rj><au>J.
Edwards.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overbarren</ent>⟦br⟧
